elements within html:
<div>    don't hold anyb semantic value, only styling purpose, block-level element
<span>   don't hold anyb semantic value, only styling purpose, inline-level element
<p>      paragraph
         <p>Steve Jobs was a co-founder and longtime chief executive officer at Apple. </p>

<h1> <h2> ... <h6> headings are used to break up contents and establish hierarchy
                   <h1>Heading Level 1</h1>
<strong> bold text & make sense
         <p><strong>Caution:</strong> Falling rocks.</p>
<b>      bold text & make no sense of emphasize
         semantically used to give strong importance to text
         <p>This recipe calls for <b>bacon</b> and <b>baconnaise</b>.</p>
<em> italicize text with emphasis
      <!-- Stressed emphasis -->
      <p>I <em>love</em> Chicago!</p>
<i> italicize but semantically alternate tone
      <!-- Alternative voice or tone -->
      <p>The name <i>Shay</i> means a gift.</p>
<title> the title of the website
